          <h2 class="main-heading">Three Simple Rules For Successful Budgeting</h2>
          <div class="section">
            <div class="sec one">
            <h2>Rule 1: Give Every Penny a Job</h2>
              <p>Be the Boss and Confidently spend your money. When you earn money, prioritize how you’ll use it, and then simply follow your plan. You’ve already mapped out a plan, so instead of stressing over every little spending decision, you’re just working your plan.</p>
              <h3>How it works?</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Earn</li>
                <li>Plan</li>
                <li>Spend Money Stress-Free</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
                <img src="/images/img-home/giveMoneyJob.png" class="sec-img"> 
              </div>
          </div>
          <div class="section-two">
            <div class="sec-two">
            <h2>Rule 2: Embrace Your True Expenses</h2>
            <p>When you follow Rule One and start giving every penny a job, your money starts to obey. It lines itself up with your priorities.<br> Now figure out infrequent large expenses, break them into manageable monthly expenses, and save money for it. So when the actual due date comes, you don't have to scratch your head or bite your fingernails. </p>
            <h3>How it works?</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Find a big, infrequent expense.</li>
                <li>Create a goal to fund it monthly.</li>
                <li>When that expense arrives, just pay it!</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>  
