        <h3 class="main-heading rule-heading">40-30-20-10 Rule Of Budgeting</h3>
        <div class="rules">
        <p>The 40 30 20 10 rule is an easy budgeting method that can help you to manage your money effectively. The basic rule of thumb is to divide your monthly after-tax income into four spending categories:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><b><u>40% For Needs:</u></b> Needs are the things necessary for survival. These include rent, bills, groceries and utilities. These are your "must-haves."</li>
          <br>
          <li><b><u>30% For Wants:</u></b> Wants are all the things you spend money on that are not absolutely essential. This includes dinning out, shopping, sporting events etc. You can cook instead of eating out, or watch sports on TV instead of getting tickets to the game.</li>
          <br>
          <li><b><u>20% For Goals:</u></b> To accomplish your goals, you need to know how to set them. Consider what you want to achieve, it could be downpayment for a new home or long vacation and break the total amount needed into monthly goals. Save the amount each month towards your goal.</li>
          <br>
          <li><b><u>10% For Investment:</u></b> This includes investing in the stock, gold, bonds etc. You should have at least 3 months of emergency savings in hand in case an unforeseen event occurs. After that, focus on retirement and meeting other financial goals down the road.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
